text:
He was blind to the internal, searing ache,
Yet his desolate gaze pleaded for patience;
He spoke in phrases from which no insight could wake.

source_text:
He knew not of the grief within that burned,
But asked forbearance with a mournful look;
Or spoke in words from which none ever learned

text:
Small lamb,
I am standing here;
Come, brush your tongue
Against my pale skin;
Let me sink my fingers
Into your downy fleece;
Let me press a kiss
To your gentle face;
With joy, we usher in the new year.

source_text:
Little lamb,
Here I am;
Come and lick
My white neck;
Let me pull
Your soft wool;
Let me kiss
Your soft face;
Merrily, merrily we welcome in the year.

Three joyous good fellows, with hearts clear of flaw
Craigdarroch, so famous for with, worth, and law;
And trusty Glenriddel, so skill’d in old coins;
And gallant Sir Robert, deep-read in old wines.

Smiles on thee, on me, on all,
Who became an infant small;
Infant smiles are His own smiles;
Heaven and earth to peace beguiles.
